This paper discusses the security aspects of the 5G protocol, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and network security (cs.NI). It also discusses the goals and requirements of 5G, which involves software engineering (cs.SE) and system engineering (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper mentions the vulnerabilities present in legacy networks, which could fall under the category of cyber security (cs.CY).
